    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-07-06</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-10-03T19:27:43Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Layoff Prevention Act of 2011 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to set forth requirements relating to short-time compensation programs to allow employers to reduce the workweek of their employees in lieu of layoffs.</p> <p>Provides for federal financing of state short-time compensation programs. Requires the Secretary of Labor to: (1) award grants to states that enact such programs; (2) develop model legislative language for use by states in developing, enacting, and implementing such programs; and (3) report to Congress and the President on their implementation.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
